0) Setup OS on raspberry first then continue with steps below.

1) Create folder: 

mkdir expo-project

2) Open folder:

cd expo-project

3) Create virtual inveroment:

python3 -m venv opencv-env

4) Open virtual inveroment:

source opencv-env/bin/activate

5) Install opencv into virtual invorment:

pip install opencv-python

6) Leave virtual invorment:

deactivate

7) Install git globally:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install git -y

8) Verify install:

git --version

9) Go to right location

cd ~/expo-project                                

